							<p>Should a credit/debit card charge be declined for any reason, then as a courtesy only and without waiving any rights or time, and using the information you provided in establishing your account, we will endeavor to contact you by email, text and/or phone (and you hereby consent to such contact).  Your credit/debit card and other billing information is held on file until all books in an order are closed (i.e. each book is returned, or bought-out and all fees paid).  BookstoreGenie reserves the right to attempt a re-charge of a declined credit/debit card periodically, at any time and for any number of attempts, to collect amounts outstanding on your account.  Additionally, if the primary credit/debit card on file with your account is declined, BookstoreGenie reserves the right to charge any of the other credit/debit cards you may have on file with your account.  BookstoreGenie is not responsible for overdraft or other penalties/fees a customer may incur for such charges (or attempted charges). In any collections action, the person listed under the Billing Information of an account is ultimately responsible for payment.  BookstoreGenie reserves the right to use a collection agency and any other means necessary to recover lost assets or any payments due. All accounts sent to collections are subject to an additional $25.00 fee.</p>
							<h2 id='processing_orders'><a href="#processing_orders">Processing Orders</a></h2>
							<p>All orders take 1-2 business days to process and ship out.  Orders placed Monday-Friday before 10 a.m. Eastern Time have the current and next business day to process and ship.  Orders placed after 10 a.m. Eastern Time will process and ship over the next two business days. Our published shipping timeframes are good faith estimates only based on our standard shipping methods.  Although we use our best efforts to meet our published timelines, we can’t guarantee what day/date you actually receive your order.</p>
							<p>Please note that there may be certain orders that we are unable to accept or otherwise process and therefore, must cancel. We reserve the right, at our sole discretion, to refuse, modify, or cancel any order for any reason.  Some situations that may result in your order being canceled include without limitation, inaccuracies or errors in product or pricing information, limitations on quantities available from our suppliers, issues identified by our credit and fraud avoidance department, or suspected violations by you of any of BookstoreGenie’s Service Policy, Privacy Policy or Terms of Use.</p>
							<p>We may also require additional verification or information before accepting or processing any order. While we will make every reasonable effort to contact you by phone or email if additional information is required, if we are unable to reach you via the contact information you provided, or you do not reply to us within the allotted time frame, we will cancel your order.  If your order is canceled after your credit/debit card has been charged, we will issue a credit to your card in the amount of the charge.  In no event will BookstoreGenie be liable for any order changed or canceled as a result of any of the foregoing.</p>
